                  <td>
                    
                    <p><font face="Verdana" color="#A80000"><b>Attention: Standards of Excellence Deadline
                    </b></font></p>
                    <p><font face="Arial" size="2">Participating schools in the
  2000-01 Standards of Excellence Program must submit their ANNUAL REPORT
  BOOKLET to the State Office on or prior to JULY 1, 2001. This ANNUAL REPORT
  must include a summation of all council activities from JUNE 1 , 2000 through
  MAY 31, 2001. Each member school received a copy of the &quot;Program&quot;
  and a &quot;Participating School Checklist&quot; with their membership packet
  which itemizes all criteria to be included in the report. Additional copies of
  those documents are available from the state office upon request.</p>
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify">The State Executive Committee
  (or their designees) will evaluate all submitted Reports and determine awards
  based upon the criteria described in the program. Awards will be announced at
  the Fall Regional Meetings and in subsequent WASC publications.</p>
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify">The State Executive Committee
  shall reserve the right to waive any requirements when a council can prove
  that, through no fault of its own, it is unable to meet certain criteria
  (including explanatory note for each item)</p>

  <h3 align="center"><font size="2">APPEAL PROCESS</font></h3>

  <p class="MsoNormal" style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify">1. The state review committee
  shall have the power to correct errors of addition. 2. A participating school
  may submit an appeal regarding its rating to the State Executive Committee. 3.
  There will be no appeal process on the interpretation of points given on any
  subjective item. 4. All appeals must be submitted in writing to the WASC State
  Office by September 15, 2001.</p>
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify">It is hoped that many schools
  will participate in this program. The created Annual Report Booklet is a
  history of yearly student council activities. It can be used to inform and
  educate various individuals and groups in the community on the services, and
  roles assumed by the student council to create a better learning environment
  for all students.
                    </font></p>
                    <p align="right"><i>&nbsp;
                    </i></p>
                    
